Note: Trying to execute the cue in this article without first understanding/ activating your <link to core article> properly is an effort in vain. 

It's hips under the bar. The sad reality is that most people will not be able to execute this even if they wanted to. This calls for keeping the glutes along with the leg musculature active rather than passively pushing the floor away. <Refer to ABC of weightlifting here>.

A cue that will work for this :
As if the bar is stationary and the floor at your will. 